import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="state", y="rate", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Obesity Rate')
    ax.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Obesity Rate: {:.2f}'.format(data['rate'].mean()))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='population', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between obesity rates and population size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='population', hue='state', multiple='stack', kde=True, palette='bright')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population sizes across states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='State', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc=2, borderaxespad=0.)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
